UNIT 2 â€“ Users, Assessments and the Risk Management Process
Unit Overview

This unit examined the role of user participation in the risk management process and compared qualitative and quantitative assessment approaches, emphasising how stakeholder involvement influences risk outcomes.

Artefacts

Peer responses

Notes on qualitative vs quantitative assessment

Open FAIR summary

Reflection

This unit highlighted that risk management is a socio-technical process rather than a purely technical one. I learned that excluding users from assessments often leads to ineffective or rejected mitigations. Understanding the strengths and weaknesses of qualitative versus quantitative approaches helped me justify methodology choices later in the module, particularly when dealing with SMEs lacking historical data.

References

Josey, A. et al. (2014). Open FAIR Risk Analysis. The Open Group.
https://www.opengroup.org/open-fair

AIRMIC (2010). A Structured Approach to ERM.
